M|code-review|Skill for reviewing code changes using the code-rv-graph knw graph.
M|code-review|Achieves 6.8× fewer tokens on reviews by reading only what matters.
M|code-review|```
M|code-review|get_minimal_context(task="<describe what changed>")
M|code-review|```
M|code-review|~100 tokens. Gives full picture. Do this BEFORE reading any files.
M|code-review|```
M|code-review|query_graph(target="<specific function/class>", detail_level="minimal")
M|code-review|```
M|code-review|Never use broad `list_*` calls. Target specific nodes.
M|code-review|```
M|code-review|detect_changes()
M|code-review|```
M|code-review|Returns risk-scored change analysis. Read the `risk_level` field first.
M|code-review|- [ ] Does this change break any callers? (check `edge` nodes)
M|code-review|- [ ] Are tests affected? (check test coverage nodes)
M|code-review|- [ ] Are there orphaned imports/functions created by this change?
M|code-review|- [ ] Does the change match the stated success criteria?
M|code-review|- [ ] Is the diff minimal — no unrelated changes?
M|code-review|- Max 5 tool calls per rv
M|code-review|- Max 800 tokens of graph ctx
M|code-review|- `next_tool_suggestions` tells you optimal next step — follow it
M|code-review|```
M|code-review|RISK: [low/medium/high]
M|code-review|CHANGED: [list of affected nodes]
M|code-review|CONCERNS: [numbered list, or "none"]
M|code-review|VERDICT: [ap / request changes]
M|code-review|```